skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "97747e63-6886-4c2c-b713-b16fdf7ad981", "value": "Line, cord or thread, especially that used for tying up parcels, etc. Also use for \"twine\", i.e. twisted thread, for the same purpose, and medieval equivalents, e.g. \"packthread\"."}

{"id": "af4602a6-4cf9-49b2-aa15-def22f201280", "value": "The white, fibrous substance surrounding the seeds of plants of the genus Gossypium, which can be spun and used in the manufacture of thread and cloth or used in its raw form as wadding or packing."}

skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:title: {"id": "aed124d7-2d19-42f5-9440-2dd6b895bfab", "value": "FISH Maritime Cargo Types Thesaurus"}
skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:description: {"id": "8d566065-a478-403b-adb0-0d1bb236998b", "value": "Used to record the type of cargo being carried by a vessel on its final voyage and often found in association with the wreck site."}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "4f4f6533-09ac-4536-ba04-574dbf590780", "value": "A herbaceous plant grown for its fibre and marijuana, a drug derivative. The fibres are used in the manufacture of rope."}
{"id": "d9c6f6d0-4582-4319-91c1-ef2aa5d2b917", "value": "Wood from non-coniferous trees, eg. oak, known for their hardness."}
{"id": "28bea472-09f5-4501-90e8-3eaed30667eb", "value": "The powdery residue left after the combustion of substances, especially wood and paper."}
{"id": "7eb5bb4c-74a7-4a66-8313-eaa0baff5105", "value": "The hard, black, heavy wood of various tropical trees native to Africa and Asia, used in furniture manufacture and for making ornaments."}
{"id": "242f4aa3-49f8-464f-b39b-8fade0b2eea9", "value": "The bark and wood of trees of the genus Aspidosperma used to produce tannin."}
{"id": "853d0835-b4a6-4838-8f07-72736ea4cb82", "value": "An exotic hardwood with great strength and durability."}
{"id": "92196ba9-5375-4439-b62b-6822770626bb", "value": "Timber from trees of the genus Juglans, used for the manufacture of furniture"}
{"id": "b225bfe0-52f0-4d8b-b486-f27fa22cd836", "value": "Wood which is soft or easily cut, particularly the wood of coniferous trees."}
{"id": "623ee51c-5859-4a57-afd5-6d8737f6fce0", "value": "Wood, cut and seasoned for use as a constructional material."}
{"id": "1194dece-03c4-478b-8fbc-97b38ebf729c", "value": "The wood from trees of the type Quercus."}
{"id": "a80f49a2-0456-4dd5-8dcc-778f42452f8b", "value": "Durable wood from the cedar tree."}
{"id": "37205c1c-bd2f-435c-b4c5-2914b5479a0d", "value": "Wood from the elm tree."}
{"id": "62ed8406-27ce-4f3a-a8f4-d23cc550a62c", "value": "The hard, heavy wood obtained from plants of the genus Guaiacum."}
{"id": "87f807b9-46eb-4949-8c46-e0faed597979", "value": "Hard wood, reddish-brown in colour with a fine-grain often used in the manufacture of furniture."}
{"id": "82914de2-3bdb-4b17-b092-5d745516d31d", "value": "Products manufactured from timber."}
{"id": "3828c96a-0133-481a-8267-008c055f6187", "value": "The hard, close-grained wood of the Box or similar trees."}
{"id": "1ae9c570-78f6-4980-a12d-0569a2620078", "value": "Timber manufactured from fir or spruce trees."}
{"id": "7c9537ab-8921-45cd-92e0-431aafae89c8", "value": "Softwood obtained from trees of the genus Pinus, often used for the manufacture of furniture."}
{"id": "627b821a-4690-4215-8aa8-45655593d69d", "value": "Porous black residue of partly burnt wood, bones etc. used as fuel or, in the form of charcoal pencils, as a tool for drawing."}
{"id": "c9c9ee69-f94b-435d-ae76-9e1a35cca20a", "value": "Small fragments of granite."}
{"id": "02160e25-4d31-4f2a-a785-af6653316f07", "value": "The seed of the flax plant pressed into cakes and used as cattle fodder."}
{"id": "598c6e08-9076-4805-9b6c-7225ca7e2974", "value": "Solid spherical objects, manufactured from stone or metal, fired from cannon."}
{"id": "a6ee0bec-c5c2-408a-aaa2-9eb587faadab", "value": "Cut human hair, usually intended for wig-making."}
{"id": "72d12018-3a92-4f9b-b7e3-e8d768719644", "value": "The fine, keratinized, flexible filaments that grow from follicles beneath the surface of the skin in mammals."}
{"id": "74658398-1253-4c4e-90da-fba21c39e143", "value": "Hair taken from animals and used in a variety of manufacturing processes."}
{"id": "15cddc18-49ae-4ae6-a9de-178e97ab919b", "value": "Dried or partially dried plums eaten as fruit."}

{"id": "560ee5ad-50aa-475a-b5aa-eec42baaf828", "value": "The hard material, consisting mainly of calcium compounds, which makes up the skeleton of vertebrates. Used for ornaments or ground for use in the manufacture of bone china."}

{"id": "eb3a2426-058e-4af1-b346-bfcbd06034d3", "value": "Soft, porous objects used in bathing and for cleaning. Originally made from the dried skeletons of marine sponges but now more commonly manufactured from synthetic foam."}
{"id": "05a896b9-4212-4539-a86d-bbf3ce368e29", "value": "The fat removed from the carcass of a whale or seal and used in the manufacture of cosmetics and as a fuel for tallow lamps."}
{"id": "dcc37259-ffa1-4d51-86c4-da588b144b17", "value": "A calcareous, hard substance, the external skeleton of marine polyps, used in the manufacture of jewellery."}
{"id": "eb82d177-511b-4363-9727-20f44dae7f08", "value": "The hides of animals, either untreated or tanned."}
{"id": "b374c3ad-1e97-4105-a45c-12173669c8b6", "value": "The hair from the coat of goats and sheep, made into yarn and used in the manufacture of woollen cloth."}
{"id": "0924c014-4cc2-4f26-bdad-daa0bea6823a", "value": "Products derived from the carcasses or hides of animals. Includes bone and ivory products, blubber and grease but not meat."}

{"id": "81bfcde2-ef62-4645-bf49-a6b0bf53b5eb", "value": "A highly-prized, hard, white, fine-grained dentine constituting the main part of the teeth of walruses, hippopotami and elephants. Used in the manufacture of ornaments and piano keys."}
{"id": "b01cf6db-010d-411f-9b61-7a3dc8ea7037", "value": "Animal skins which have been treated by tanning or similar."}
{"id": "6ac69320-3db2-4404-840a-2aefd8d0bdd9", "value": "Product of boiled blubber"}
{"id": "084b1e3b-f738-4f63-9861-e63ced7ad158", "value": "Oil obtained from the rendered blubber of whales, used as a fuel in old oil lamps."}
{"id": "6ff820f4-4d41-43ec-a653-a64fee80082c", "value": "Bone like material which grows in a branch-like fashion on the heads of male deer and reindeers in general."}
{"id": "e9827284-06da-4c5f-bd47-fd2efb08dc05", "value": "A malleable water repellant substance created by animals or as a coating to parts of plants."}
{"id": "77f8463d-9c60-49d1-9588-97c81eb05593", "value": "A fatty substance rendered from animal fat and used in the manufacture of soap, candles and for dressing leather."}
{"id": "4d71c438-aa61-4a17-bc95-23aecc110a91", "value": "The bony outgrowths found on the heads of mammals used for display or combat used for a variety of purposes."}
{"id": "490be68b-09fc-4a52-86bb-ab99106e2ad1", "value": "Fat from an animal used to lubricate objects."}
{"id": "4770262d-f22c-490c-84fb-8d29240466dc", "value": "Clay used in the manufacture of fire bricks."}
{"id": "9235f334-482a-4d0f-b12e-588485657422", "value": "Tracked, armoured fighting vehicles designed for front-line combat."}
{"id": "0b87e9e7-fe66-4c53-9e6d-75823ca95add", "value": "Machinery and parts for the manufacture or assembly of military tanks, i.e. armoured vehicles."}
{"id": "275b14d8-7b52-4943-a2c7-061cff5adf81", "value": "Seeds of any of the various related plants of the leguminous plant Vicia faba."}
{"id": "2c6cc5d2-f985-48a2-a9c3-019dcc49647c", "value": "Small seeds of the leguminous plant Lens culinaris, eaten in stews and soups."}
{"id": "9d2f0d51-0f97-443a-af9d-48847d8a83be", "value": "The fruit of certain varieties of the plant Capsicum Annum eaten as vegetables."}
{"id": "c8bb76de-60d9-4163-9836-235095ae6624", "value": "Any plants which are grown to be eaten. Includes parts of plants, especially roots and leaves."}
{"id": "abb4e15f-f033-47d3-ae6e-646948b06e19", "value": "The plant, Allium sativum, whose bulb is used for culinary purposes."}
{"id": "2fb4cc15-a170-4617-a1b9-d5330b847207", "value": "The plant, Allium cepa, whose bulb is used, usually for culinary purposes."}
{"id": "42e92416-6499-4acd-8933-4dcfe4c6a194", "value": "The round seeds of the plant Pisum sativum which grow in pods and are eaten as a vegetable."}
{"id": "d43d8be1-ac47-4929-ad5b-dd767d84c811", "value": "The edible tubers of plants of the family Ipomoea Batatas eaten as a vegetable."}
{"id": "6decc788-a79c-476a-8633-df93c1d4af1f", "value": "A fine, soft fibre produced by silkworms and used to make thread for textiles. Also the cloth made from this thread."}
{"id": "e540e6e1-140b-4705-b9ba-7c43930f909c", "value": "Supplies owned by, or for the use of, the government."}
{"id": "f0cb0416-0fad-43c7-9a43-37d00aa7c50a", "value": "Equipment, including uniforms, small arms and field pieces, used by the armed forces."}
{"id": "d6faf385-9127-42e5-bc16-3c380d602dbd", "value": "Receptacles, including boxes, barrels etc., designed to contain something."}
{"id": "5c56872b-2c00-448d-995f-a5947e520e76", "value": "Thick ropes and rigging."}
{"id": "5568c236-3f83-4967-8521-337cf9125503", "value": "A three dimensional representation of a figure, whether animal or human, produced by carving, casting sculpting or similar."}
{"id": "2d15db29-f60a-4268-8336-dfa259aa7672", "value": "Equipment and parts used in the manufacture of railway tracks, locomotives and rolling stock."}
{"id": "b773a412-96f2-48b6-9302-b6d2522de8ce", "value": "Use for cargoes which are not specified."}
{"id": "1f01f4cf-f039-47eb-a23f-6f8cb8b7c1fc", "value": "Naturally occuring substances eg. coal and salt, obtained by mining."}
{"id": "77978f51-ac3b-4b90-92dd-71c136846aad", "value": "Supplies including food, drink and equipment necessary for a journey."}

{"id": "64809cbf-0373-4056-8d27-00cad6eb6488", "value": "Any material, including gold, silver, copper, tin etc. which is ductile, malleable, usually lustrous and a good conductor of heat and electricity."}
{"id": "73d792ee-aa62-4bdc-9b17-55655a16e33e", "value": "Includes chemical and natural fertilizers and waste products. use more specific term."}
{"id": "29cb4c76-1e5b-465b-a41c-e386b6588c6e", "value": "Animals and products made from the carcasses and hides of dead animals."}

{"id": "6e1ad404-a91f-4f3a-8069-a8d6a329936a", "value": "Articles, usually woven from coarse fibres or made from hard wearing materials (eg. rubber or cork) used to protect the floor or for lying, sitting or kneeling on."}
{"id": "af375578-140a-480b-88d8-79432cef2922", "value": "Items that have been through a manufacturing process. Use specific type where known."}
{"id": "235c4c94-7b81-497a-ae50-e8d14c88bb63", "value": "Materials used for the construction of buildings, vehicles or other objects."}
{"id": "19a840d2-e34d-4aff-aae2-1a5f8d0659e4", "value": "Food, usually hay or straw, kept for the feeding of animals."}
{"id": "1a6d8a7c-1ada-4d86-84d6-57d72c1c07ab", "value": "Includes all forms of paper and any products manufactured from it."}
{"id": "6b9d0381-72e9-443f-ba58-c53e9b74b442", "value": "Letters and parcels transported on behalf of the dispatchers by the postal services."}
{"id": "4e6997c4-e7f1-4430-9789-a61257f45a5c", "value": "A heavy substance, usually gravel, sand or lead, placed in the bilge of a ship or boat to provide stability."}

{"id": "0e8478e8-d5ff-4fb9-92f7-7fd866732146", "value": "Materials used to equip and fit out a ship. Includes masts, spars, rigging etc. Use only where evidence is less specific, otherwise use most relevant term."}
{"id": "fcd19b81-becc-44a1-901c-db7ffc4a7ebc", "value": "Substances, including acids, alkalis etc. obtained by or used in a chemical process."}
{"id": "e9122e8d-38b4-44fc-8225-a09f1e1c17f0", "value": "Materials or goods which have been produced wholly or in part from oil, e.g. petroleum."}

{"id": "d144af1f-97e4-4e2d-a12f-6ee112e43b2b", "value": "Colour or dye, often in powder form, from natural mineral or vegetable sources (e.g. ochre) or created through chemical process (e.g. lamp black)."}
{"id": "eef9b554-760e-4615-beec-e9310ab53363", "value": "Human beings. Use more specific type where known."}
{"id": "b53fe1c8-17bd-463e-9d45-28996a122ca2", "value": "Clothing, cloth and woven fabric manufactured from either natural or artificial fibres."}
{"id": "acdd01b0-6cef-4307-b083-fedbc6128ae5", "value": "Materials or substances, including petrol, firewood etc., used as a source of heat or power."}
{"id": "80ac323b-d320-4973-959b-db87162934c3", "value": "Articles of value particularly those made with precious metals and precious stones, usually worn for adornment."}
{"id": "4b429d3f-d734-49ec-bf86-5a256db670c6", "value": "Includes all trees, flowers, vegetables etc. and any products manufactured from them."}
{"id": "f476edbe-e313-4a06-ba76-4c004a2fe4f0", "value": "This is the top term for the thesaurus."}
{"id": "40dc037e-5895-4da0-9210-b82136bb222c", "value": "Includes raw and processed."}
{"id": "31a5d63e-4d69-4050-939b-c36bb786b5a2", "value": "Fabric manufactured from fibrous materials, consolidated by heat and compression so that the fibres become matted together."}
{"id": "fe9290ef-ea33-45ad-9f96-0e300feacf66", "value": "An alloy, traditionally of tin and lead but now of tin, antimony and copper, used for domestic utensils."}

{"id": "839031e9-1442-43c3-8235-5af5edc5cbe9", "value": "Sedimentary clay with smectite mineral properties, originally used for the cleansing [\"fulling\"] of cloth; in the 20th century it was used for a wider range of industrial applications."}
{"id": "f782d091-dcc8-497e-aa2a-a90d5638d20a", "value": "Large fish, native to the North Atlantic and adjacents seas which has been fished since the Middle Ages."}
{"id": "d9e0d091-b190-4750-a143-c62bf7b8f54b", "value": "Items of crockery and cutlery which are used whilst dining, either to eat with or for table decoration."}
{"id": "03bbabc1-a530-4acc-b7d2-2f5d83fc9741", "value": "Instruments for measuring and displaying time. Often manufactured as a piece of furniture e.g.a grandfather clock."}

{"id": "a89f2c22-acc3-4a11-b1ee-ca28b64fae73", "value": "Small pieces of wood, tipped with a chemical composition which ignites when rubbed against a rough or, if safety matches, prepared surface. Normally contained within a small box."}

{"id": "8097fb6a-e5b1-4cf0-8d43-dd7f2ece39e8", "value": "Ceramic vessels produced out of wet clay which is shaped ad dried or fired to harden. In some cases other materials like sand are added to the clay."}
{"id": "852a13ac-9dbe-48c3-b0f8-4de12c83f9b7", "value": "Movable, usually functional, articles normally found in the home."}
{"id": "da7d063d-89f2-4760-b86c-60f11d2da4ea", "value": "Goods, including portable objects and furniture, commonly found in the home."}
{"id": "b6180036-23e5-4af1-a223-f3b5ea95a79a", "value": "Holders for one or more candles, usually of metal or pewter."}
{"id": "56427694-acfc-4b3a-8e4b-34b51a1af933", "value": "A body of wax or tallow, usually formed into a long, thin, cylindrical shape enclosing a wick and burnt to produce light."}

{"id": "1cea9771-8ab5-4350-920b-f64d614f951e", "value": "\"Looking glasses\", up to and including the medieval period made of polished steel or other reflective metals; later a piece of glass with a reflective coating, e.g. silver or aluminium."}

{"id": "4cceed98-2aa5-4fe1-8022-f1063c5742b2", "value": "A cleansing agent, manufactured by reacting natural oils and fats with a strong alkali. Nowadays, formed into bars with added colouring and perfume."}
{"id": "9b3c27d3-f32a-41cb-bcd9-6d30a01dc879", "value": "An odourless, tasteless powder obtained from cereals and potatoes, used for stiffening fabric."}
{"id": "ad7aa931-48bd-478b-a7c6-f98a1d081662", "value": "Optical and/or navigational instruments with powerful lenses for observing remote objects or used in astronomy."}
{"id": "ec119240-8560-4ce6-84bd-a37475171fc1", "value": "Instruments for determining position at sea, e.g. compasses, sextants."}

{"id": "2a7bc647-1abf-404f-8d80-e12c00581602", "value": "Pieces of material, usually decorated, used as standards, for signalling or for decoration. Often used as a symbol of a particular nation eg. the Union Flag of Great Britain."}
{"id": "81eb149b-9fff-491f-8e4c-ec75e169a41e", "value": "Fish eggs, e.g. from cod or, for example, caviar."}
{"id": "b2951aff-624b-4651-9067-c49b31e5355e", "value": "A reddish metal used in alloys, coins and the construction and electronics industries."}
{"id": "612a37a6-4c8f-451b-a7e6-d7719fb81dd8", "value": "Solid bars made from pure Copper metal."}
{"id": "8f758a8c-fb00-4255-ac9f-4e5de22b8a04", "value": "Partially decomposed granite used to produce a glaze for porcelain."}
{"id": "419ced40-702b-4c35-837b-9ad5089fa9de", "value": "The large, pointed teeth, made of ivory, which are specially developed to protrude from the mouth of elephants."}

{"id": "d0bc76ca-2873-4719-a285-a693f9ced26b", "value": "Traditionally a mineral that could be used for striking fire but now a term commonly used to refer to various sulphides, especially iron disulphide."}
{"id": "90e49f56-9240-48ad-8ef7-3ec51c7f197f", "value": "Non bituminous coal"}
{"id": "e61ebe20-8217-48bd-82f4-ae1919ae3661", "value": "Flat stones used to create flat surfaces, e.g. pavements."}
{"id": "0af5150a-6331-40c8-8765-18bfe35ea4e4", "value": "Products manufactured from stone."}
{"id": "28f94fda-91f1-4831-bd3c-404cde4349a2", "value": "Stones used to edge a pavement or raised path."}
{"id": "c825a84c-8183-4df5-ba12-e81f47b5dbf8", "value": "Thin plates of slate, usually rectangular in shape, used as roofing tiles."}
{"id": "da7a4aeb-3dde-449e-858b-84336ee68290", "value": "A white, caustic solid obtained by heating limestone and used in the preparation of mortar and cement."}
{"id": "14281dfe-9491-45d1-9a93-ab55b014f3e2", "value": "Worked pieces of stone. Use more specific type of stone where known."}
{"id": "c4bd3c0e-ba3e-4232-874e-8fe60345b08b", "value": "Powder made from particles of stone used in mining to make the coal dust in the air less combustible."}
{"id": "7a1fe2d7-f9d5-4121-b670-938604c4dfd6", "value": "Citrus fruit, usually green."}
{"id": "b29d8f47-1d64-476a-9ccb-0454591c5f44", "value": "A semi metal, poisonous element used in a variety of industrial processes and in some medicinal preparations."}

{"id": "ccfa01d6-aca5-43ef-822c-da506ba2055a", "value": "Also spelt \"oszemundt\" and other variants. Low-grade cast iron in the form of balls or spheres, produced in small workshops and exported across the North Sea and Baltic region. Particularly associated with 16th century Sweden."}
{"id": "865300e0-e61d-4a5a-8cee-de182456ee56", "value": "Large blocks of timber used to support railway tracks."}
{"id": "88b4bf10-55ac-4db5-aa00-c0c13e02036e", "value": "Fibres obtained from plants and used in the manufacture of ropes, sacking, canvas etc."}
{"id": "fc3e6198-5c69-4cf5-a19d-355c584bb54c", "value": "A flammable liquid that occurs naturally and is also now distilled."}
{"id": "1035df04-5294-49ec-8884-3181f315890f", "value": "Drinks containing alcohol, an intoxicating substance found in fermented or distilled liquids."}
{"id": "31da04cf-79ac-4dda-9a7b-bfcf3f266fdf", "value": "Oil manufactured from fish."}
{"id": "fc8c52b2-1a2d-4f06-9339-96c9473413ff", "value": "Oil produced from the pulp of olives."}
{"id": "8a40e47e-9b0b-4f04-ae37-f65b9c0b52c1", "value": "Oil obtained from the flesh of the coconut and used in ointments, soaps etc."}
{"id": "9326d229-84d9-4370-9f59-85efd0de2432", "value": "A sweet fluid substance, the nectar of flowers, gathered and worked up for food by insects such as bees."}
{"id": "8f5fc5ff-3f95-4ea1-9050-4e97a7d6dcd1", "value": "An uncrystallized syrup, produced as part of the sugar refining process. Used as a food additive and in the production of rum."}
{"id": "f54eaaac-5c73-4caf-88af-74b16912f3d3", "value": "A sour tasting liquid, produced from wine and other liquors, used as a preservative, in pickling, or as a flavouring for food."}
{"id": "62711d3a-2153-4abe-910b-4edbd20ed5b6", "value": "A clear liquid that forms oceans, rivers etc."}
{"id": "2aada765-1c0b-400b-bd42-8840a77191a7", "value": "Oil derived from palms, used for a variety of purposes."}
{"id": "3cf1c0e0-eebb-4ec7-a5e4-8e42e15ca1f1", "value": "A fluid substance. Use for unspecified liquids only, where known use more specific type."}
{"id": "c4b5edb1-adb5-4519-bd66-91446b0a755c", "value": "Zinc, now mainly used for smelted zinc but has been used to include zinc ores."}
{"id": "c6d7a261-ecbf-4034-8a7b-b0bba9532b94", "value": "People who are considered to be the property of someone else and who are bound to obedience."}
{"id": "4a0d4511-4a0d-4980-9839-e634086247b5", "value": "The heartwood of a leguminous tree from which an extract is obtained. The extract being used for dyeing."}
{"id": "9ae3c7e3-c348-4e82-bf96-2af844a1a2e0", "value": "Wood used to produce a dye."}
{"id": "8fb45548-67cf-47c2-9433-49d3496451a9", "value": "The powdery residue resulting from the combustion of a substance eg. wood and used for various manufacturing processes."}
{"id": "2d5b155d-f6e4-4e20-bd30-48ab92c514cd", "value": "The latex of plants tacky in its normal state and elastic after treatment. Used for a variety of purposes."}

{"id": "fa748062-8dbe-4e14-88ec-2f998c6f3996", "value": "A preparation made from the evaporated juice of the rhizome of the plant Glycyrrhiza glabra, used medicinally and as a sweet, usually in the form of a black, chewy substance."}
{"id": "51c561af-07d0-46dc-9764-b5a38ff6e79e", "value": "A substance secreted by some plants which hardens upon drying but is soluble in water."}
